page.title: 14OTHER VERTEBRATES
page.content: THE DYKES,MARSHES,CARR AND WOODLAND OF THE BLOCK PROVIDE A WIDE VARIETY OF HABITATS FOR SMALL VERTEBRATES.THE FOLLOWING ARE KNOWN TO INHABIT OR VISIT THE AREA:- HEDGEHOG,COMMON SHREW,PIGMY SHREW, WATER SHREW,MOLE,DAUBENTON'S BAT, PIPISTRELLE,RABBIT,BROWN HARE,GREY SQUIRREL,WATER VOLE,FIELD VOLE,WOOD MOUSE,HOUSE MOUSE,BROWN RAT,COYPU, FOX,STOAT,WEASEL,COMMON SEAL. GRASS SNAKE,ADDER,COMMON LIZARD, SLOW WORM. COMMON FROG,COMMON TOAD,SMOOTH NEWT, GREAT CRESTED NEWT. EEL,PIKE,PERCH,RUFFE,BREAM,SILVER BREAM,ROACH,RUDD,DACE,TENCH,GUDGEON, THREE-SPINED STICKLEBACK,FLOUNDER, SMELT,SEA-TROUT.
